!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

commercial /kəˈmɜːʃəl/

(commercials) 

1. ADJ Commercial means involving or relating to the buying and selling of goods. 商业的 

例： Baltimore in its heyday was a major centre of industrial and commercial activity. 巴尔的摩在其鼎盛时期曾是工商业活动的主要中心。 

2. ADJ Commercial organizations and activities are concerned with making money or profits, rather than, for example, with scientific research or providing a public service. 商业化的 

例： The company has indeed become more commercial over the past decade. 这个公司在过去的十年里确实已变得越来越商业化了。 

例： Conservationists in Chile are concerned over the effect of commercial exploitation of forests. 智利的自然保护者对森林商业化开发的后果感到担忧。 

3. commercially ADV 商业化地 

例： The plane will be commercially viable if 400 can be sold. 这飞机若能售出400架从商业上看就可行。 

4. ADJ A commercial product is made to be sold to the public. 商业性的 [ADJ n] 

例： They are the leading manufacturer in both defence and commercial products. 他们在防御性和商业性的产品方面都是领先的制造商。 

5. commercially ADV 商业性地 

例： It was the first commercially available machine to employ artificial intelligence. 这是第一台具有商业价值的人工智能机器。 

6. ADJ A commercial vehicle is a vehicle used for carrying goods, or passengers who pay. 商用的 

例： The route is used every day by many hundreds of commercial vehicles. 这条路线每天都有成百辆商用车通过。 

7. ADJ Commercial television and radio are paid for by the broadcasting of advertisements, rather than by the government. 商业化的 (电视或广播) 

例： There were no commercial radio stations until 

1920. 直到1920年才有了商业电台。 

8. ADJ Commercial is used to describe something such as a film or a type of music that it is intended to be popular with the public, and is not very original or of high quality. 商业化的 (电影或音乐) 

例： There's a feeling among a lot of people that music has become too commercial. 许多人都感到音乐已变得太商业化了。 

9. N-COUNT A commercial is an advertisement that is broadcast on television or radio. 电视或电台广告 

例： Turn the channel – there are too many commercials. 转换一下频道–太多广告了。

